data.title: Bryun Parham - Football 2023
data.meta_description: Football 2023 - Bryun Parham: The Official Athletic Site of San Jose State Athletics, partner of WMT Digital. The most comprehensive coverage of San Jose State on the web with rosters, schedules, scores, highlights, game recaps and more!
data.text:
AWARDS:

All-Mountain West Honorable Mention (2023)

Third Team Phil Steele's Postseason Mountain West Team (2023)

Fourth Team Phil Steele's Preseason Mountain West Team (2023)

2023:

Led the Spartans with career-high 106 tackles, five tackles for loss, 2.5 sacks, three pass breakups, one interception, one forced fumble and two fumble recoveries

Parham finished second in the Mountain West conference with 60 solo tackles

12 tackles including 10 solo and quarterback hurry in EasyPost Hawai'i Bowl against Coastal Carolina (12/23)

Eight tackles, 1.0 sacks and 2.0 TFL's at UNLV (11/25)

Nine tackles, first career INT, a sack and 1.5 TFL's against SDSU (11/18)

Six tackles, one PBU and 0.5 TFL's against No. 25 Fresno St. (11/11)

Four tackles and one PBU at Hawai'i (10/28)

Seven tackles and a QB hurry vs. Utah State (10/21)

Eight tackles at UNM (10/14)

Career-high two fumble recoveries, one forced fumble, 12 tackles at Boise State (10/07)

11 tackles vs. Air Force (9/22)

11 tackles including 0.5 TFL's at Toledo (9/16)

Led team with nine tackles, plus 0.5 sacks and 0.5 TFL at No. 6 USC (8/26)

2022:

Career-high's with 93 tackles, six tackles for loss, two forced fumbles and three sacks

Five tackles, one tackle for loss, one sack and one forced fumble in Potato Bowl vs. EMU (12/20)

Six tackles vs. Hawai'i (11/26)

Career-best 14 tackles plus a sack at Utah State (11/19)

Nine tackles and a pass break up at San Diego State (11/12)

One tackle and one pass break up vs. CSU (11/05)

Career-high 10 tackles, first career sack and career-high 2.0 tackles for loss vs. Nevada (10/29)

Seven tackles and a forced fumble at Fresno State (10/15)

Had five tackles vs. UNLV (10/7)

Combined with Noah Wright on safety, plus added four tackles at Wyoming (10/01)

Started and had career-best six tackles vs. WMU (9/24)

Had three tackles including 0.5 for loss at Auburn (9/10)

Had four tackles against Portland State (9/1)

2021:

Made seven appearances this season

Took the field as a starter against Colorado State (11/5)

Credited 19 tackles and 1.0 tackles for loss

HIGH SCHOOL:

A two-time CaiHiSports.com all-state honoree for Long Beach Poly (Coach Stephen Barbee)

A first-team, All-State choice in 2021 and a 2019 third-team All-State selection

Played as an inside and outside linebacker, saw action as a defensive end, and was an occasional running back on offense

Credited with 129 tackles, 31.5 tackles for loss, 10.5 quarterback sacks, a pass interception and four pass break-ups in 16 games played

Named the 2021 Moore League Most Valuable Player, an All-C.I.F. Division II Southern Section honoree, and a 2019 first-team All-Moore League choice
